UML:TaggedValue.value: The issuer of the ticket can define what part of the ticket, if any, may be accessed by which group of other users
The end user can agree of receiving advertisements from Service providers, related to the key words specified in the ticket
The Service providers can provide advertisement along the tickets data
The Operators should be able to identify the tickets with overdue deadline
The users can accept or reject the proposed completion date and costs
The operators should be able to track the unassigned tickets, analyse the reasons for this lack of interest

The developers should be able to specify the time when they can provide a solution and if applicable, the estimated costs.
The end users can accept or reject them.
The developers should be able to report their progress against the defined deadlines
The users can set deadlines for timely resolving the reported issue

UML:UseCase.name: Contribution to the Service/Service Provider appreciation

UML:TaggedValue.value: Contribution to the Service/Service Provider appreciation

The end users can express their satisfaction with the help received on the reported problem. This evaluation contributes to the evaluation of the Service and Service Provider shown on the Service page at uStore

In order to ensure higher user satisfaction, the ticket could be sent to multiple service providers/developers that can handle the request
The TS should support setting deadlines for completing the tickets and the deelopers/service providers working on given ticket should be able to report the progress
